.TH "batadv_bla_loopdetect_check" 9 "batadv_bla_loopdetect_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_bla_loopdetect_check \- check and handle a detected loop
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_bla_loopdetect_check
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *primary_if "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "skb" 12
the packet to check
.IP "primary_if" 12
interface where the request came on
.IP "vid" 12
the VLAN ID of the frame
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks if this packet is a loop detect frame which has been sent by us,
throws an uevent and logs the event if that is the case.
.SH "RETURN"
true if it is a loop detect frame which is to be dropped, false
otherwise.
